LEX The Chronicler.

"First Person" is a person.
"Chronicler" is a person.
"Verdict Line" is a text.
"Handoff" is a text.
"Draft" is a text.

The First Person appoints the Chronicler, fixes the Verdict Line, and fixes the Handoff.

CLAUSE: Record.
The Chronicler may register the Verdict Line, and afterwards register the Handoff, and afterwards file a Draft.
